  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dbd\u0dca \u0daf\u0ddc\u0da9\u0db8\u0dca \u0dc0\u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dbd\u0dda \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dbd\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "There are no vines on the vines for orange cultivation",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "In order to earn dollars for this country, the Ministry of Agriculture introduced to the farmers many years ago that the orange plantations are under threat of destruction.",
        "Cultivation of vine oranges is carried out by a large number of people in this area and with the current extremely dry weather conditions these days, the growers of Galewela Bambaragaswewa area point out that because kerosene and diesel are not provided to water the vine oranges, the harvest of this cultivation is destroyed and falls under the trees. .",
        "These farmers point out that the Department of Agriculture has introduced this economic cultivation by spending a lot of money and in such a case, if the responsible authorities of the Agriculture Department or the government intervene to provide at least some fuel to the fruit cultivation that receives these dollars, not only the farmers but also the country will receive dollars."
      ],
      "title_ents": [],
